post_text:
SLVUSD: Please Share
Information from the Santa Cruz County Office Education:



In an effort to help families finding shelter we have created a survey to connect people who need shelter with those who are offering it.

· If you and your family are in need of a place to stay and/or park a vehicle or

· if you would like to offer a place to stay and/or park a vehicle...

Please complete this survey:

https://sccoe.link/fire



Also, please note that the County has announced the opening of shelters at the Santa Cruz Civic and Santa Cruz County Fairgrounds.



For information on accommodations for evacuees, please call Red Cross at 1-866-272-2237.



If you need assistance evacuating animals, please call 831-471-1182.



Please keep yourselves and your loved ones safe.

Dr. Laurie Bruton,
SLVUSD Superintendent

post_text:
SLVUSD: Food Services. What SLVUSD Food services are doing for the County. Stronger Together!
We have a driver, Duane, who goes to Scott's Valley every morning and every afternoon to pick up the county breakfasts and lunches. He then takes the food to the County Office on Emeline. Where the food is divided in boxes for each shelter. Then loaded into our District vans. Our District drivers Tyler, Wendi, Paul and Alicia. Deliver the food to several shelters throughout Santa Cruz County. These drivers do the route twice a day.
The process is repeated for lunch time.
Kris, from Santa Cruz City Schools. Dispatches her drivers. Those drivers do the Watsonville area shelters.
We will be doing this through the summer.

SLVFFF: SLVFFF. San Lorenzo Valley Families For Food UPDATE: Hi Troops! Last week SLVFFF distributed $10,000 dollars worth of Safeway food cards. We have raised $25,000 so far. This is an ongoing effort. Please contribute when you are able. Stronger Together!

Also grab your favorite beverage, turn on your best video and speakers, and tune in Wednesday night @7pm to SLVUSD FB page for a Watch Party SLV ROCKS FOOD FOR FAMILIES: Featuring local talented artists such Coffis Brothers, Steve Sofranko, Taylor Rae, Sydney Gorham, Cosmic Pinball, SLV Teacher Band, Alli Battaglia & The Musical Brewing Co and Fishhook. SLVUSD will be hosting this weekly Watch Party each Wednesday night at 7pm to help raise funds for SLVFFF.

Here is the teaser again from Jesse Daniel and Taylor Rae.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bK1iwnL6NQM&list=PLWRXIDuoDKZXAD0iXmeV2XP8_1RKkK7bP&index=17&t=0s

Thanks for you contributions

post_text:
SLVUSD: WE ARE SLV AWARD! Mr. Jeff Kitts, IT Director

Ms. Rachel Ogilvie, Computer Resource Specialist

Mr. Paul Owens, Computer Resource Specialist

Mr. Schiermeyer, Deputy Superintendent, nominated the IT Department and read the nomination form as follows, “The IT Department has been integral in supporting our District’s Instructional Program. From upgrading our broadband internet services/access points to supporting teachers with Chromebooks carts, to TV installations for Apple TV to curriculum updates to support student and teacher log-ins. In addition, they supported the implementation of our new VOIP (phone, horn and clocks) system throughout the District. They also supported upgrades to District websites and other technology needs on a daily basis.”

Dr. Bruton, Superintendent, added, "We are always grateful for the IT Department and how they are ready to assist us with our technology issues at any time."
text:
SLVUSD: WE ARE SLV AWARD! Mr. Jeff Kitts, IT Director

Ms. Rachel Ogilvie, Computer Resource Specialist

Mr. Paul Owens, Computer Resource Specialist

Mr. Schiermeyer, Deputy Superintendent, nominated the IT Department and read the nomination form as follows, “The IT Department has been integral in supporting our District’s Instructional Program. From upgrading our broadband internet services/access points to supporting teachers with Chromebooks carts, to TV installations for Apple TV to curriculum updates to support student and teacher log-ins. In addition, they supported the implementation of our new VOIP (phone, horn and clocks) system throughout the District. They also supported upgrades to District websites and other technology needs on a daily basis.”

Dr. Bruton, Superintendent, added, "We are always grateful for the IT Department and how they are ready to assist us with our technology issues at any time."

post_text:
SLVUSD: Community:
Thrill the World! 2019
Thrill the World.jpeg
Rehearsals
When: Thursdays: Oct.3 and Oct. 17 and Fridays Oct. 11 and Oct. 25 from 3:00-4:00pm
Where: Multipurpose Room on the District Office (Quail Hollow) campus
No need to sign up ahead of time. Just show up.

This event was founded in 2006 in Toronto, and has now spread to six continents. Every October people in cities around the world dance to "Thriller" at exactly the same time. Preparation and counting down worldwide is part of the fun, but the feeling of being connected to others and dancing together as one is a Thrill like no other! This year the event will be held in Santa Cruz on Saturday, October 26, 2018 at the Louden Nelson Center lawn at 3pm sharp. There is also an option to perform in a flashmob on Halloween in Ben Lomond.

--
Amber Walker
Quail Hollow Integrated Arts

SLVHS: First SLVHS Aquaponics Farmers Market Fundraiser coming Saturday, October 5th!
The SLVHS Aquaponics class will put on the first SLVHS Farmers Market in front of the school on Saturday, October 5th from 1:00 pm to 6:00 pm on Saturday, October 5th. Students will be selling the produce they grow in our very own aquaponic greenhouse.
Items available will include lettuce, basil, mushrooms, chives, succulents, cucumbers, and more. They will be sold by our student farmers and volunteers. All proceeds will go to funding our greenhouse and program. Donations will be also accepted.

Tri- Campus: This is an important message from San Lorenzo Valley Unified School District. The District would like to thank you for your understanding during a General Lockdown that was put in place on the tri-campus today as a precautionary measure due to potential activity in the area. This General Lockdown has been lifted and all students and staff are safe. As a reminder this is an early out day for Middle School and High School students – middle school is released at 1:40 and high school is released at 2:01pm.
Thank you!

post_text:
FYI: If we missed you today.
PHONES DOWN AT DISTRICT OFFICE
Please read - important news
Due to a scheduled PG&E Power Outage, the SLV District Office and tri-campus do not have phones for Monday, July 29th.
Please excuse the fact that the District Office phones are saying that they have been disconnected. It is because we have a VOIP (Voice Over Internet Protocol) phone system and when the internet is disrupted due to power outages, etc., we lose our phone system. We do have the capability of plugging a single phone into our fax machine (land line), however, it would operate using our fax machine phone number and many of you would probably not think to call in to us using that number.

Please accept our apologies. Because it is still summer time, we did not think many community members would be trying to contact us. We should be back up and running smoothly tomorrow, Tuesday, July 30th.
